import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(values='people', index='year', columns='age', aggfunc='sum')
    sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population by year and age?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
